I absolutely love your videos.  I can only imagine how much work and time you put into them.  Things change so fast, so when I try this tutorial 7 months after the video was made. I have had to do some modifications.  I am using firebase v9, which seems to be quite different. I have to use a slightly different syntax to pull the data from the database.

First. I have to import as follows: 
import { collection, query, orderBy, onSnapshot } from "firebase/firestore"

Then this is my mounted method:
  mounted() {
    const q = query(collection(db, "qweets"), orderBy("date"))
    const unsubscribe = onSnapshot(q, (snapshot) => {
      snapshot.docChanges().forEach((change) => {
        let qweetChange = change.doc.data()
        if (change.type === "added") {
            console.log("New qweet: ", qweetChange)
            this.qweets.unshift(qweetChange)
        }
        if (change.type === "modified") {
            console.log("Modified qweet: ", qweetChange)
        }
        if (change.type === "removed") {
            console.log("Removed qweet: ", qweetChange)
        }
      })
    })
  },

